init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world was in ruins, and the only nations that were left were the ones that were able to protect themselves from the war.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The only problem was that the United States was in no shape to do so.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were able to get the world back up and running, but it was a very slow process.
